      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): treat generic 'LLM request failed' error as transient server_error",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nTreat generic 'LLM request failed' error as transient server_error for retry/fallback\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/provider-request-error-classifier.ts`: Add 'LLM request failed' to the transient server_error check\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: A cron job calling a model that returns `\"LLM request failed.\"` previously got classified as null (permanent error, no retry, no fallback). Now it maps to `server_error` so retry and fallback can fire.\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\n```text\n$ node -e 'const text = \"LLM request failed.\"; console.log(\"Input:\", text); console.log(\"Includes LLM request failed:\", text.includes(\"LLM request failed\")); console.log(\"Before: classified as null (permanent error)\"); console.log(\"After:  classified as server_error (transient, retryable)\");'\nInput: LLM request failed.\nIncludes LLM request failed: true\nBefore: classified as null (permanent error)\nAfter:  classified as server_error (transient, retryable)\n```\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end with a live cron job hitting a model returning this error.\n\n## Risk\n\n- [x] Backwards compatible (additive check)\n- [x] Only affects retry classification\n\nCloses: #93931",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93931-model-fallbacks-never-engage",
